There was such a stark contrast between how she was when she focused on brewing hot cocoa for us – lost, relaxed, distant, or perhaps dreaming, stirring the pot without a thought for it ; her movements were automatic – and her attitude when she saw me.
She hasn’t lost that joy. Today still, she loves me and loves being with me.


