Various[c] musings on how life must feel for those trapped in a shelter, with no hope of ever seeing the outside world; to be stuck with the same people all your life, to breathe the same recycled air, and to spend your time repairing the same systems that keep you alive; becoming so attached to the society people once had during better times that you do everything in your power to keep it in place, with no room for growth.
